ction between these two galaxy populations. We also investigate rest-frame\nUV and optical morphologies of our ALMA sources with deep HST images, and find\nthat ~30-40% of our ALMA sources are classified as major mergers. This\nindicates that dusty starbursts are triggered not only by the major mergers but\nalso the other mechanism(s).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Mar 2017 22:43:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Aug 2017 05:19:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 2 Oct 2017 05:27:01 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 13 Oct 2017 04:53:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-06"}
